SIDE NOTE: SHIPPED MERCH
This show (#OKODallas) was different due to the fact of complications behind the scenes with the vip merch. VIPs received their lanyards but other merch will be shipped. Please check your emails. We are not sure how many shows are going to be like this

MERCH:
You will receive your vip merch at the beginning. It is the same merch as the tour back in September.

MASTERCLASS:
The Masterclass was just Ryan on stage breaking down a song. You are able to ask him questions throughout the session and there’s a big q&a at the end (with only Ryan). The class was rough 20 mins long.
+ to add to this, it’s the same way as the m&g, but just a giant group photo.

MASTERCLASS PHOTOS: 
Everyone who had Masterclass was split into roughly 2 groups. In total there was about 60 people who had masterclass (we think, we will find out when Masterclass photos come out so don’t take my word). U get a socially distanced group photo with them.

MEET AND GREET:
The m&g was socially distanced. The exact same way as it was done in the first leg of the tour back in September. U can give them gifts but not directly. U are able to show it to them and then give it to their manager or someone on their team.

DODGEBALL:
There were two rounds. The winner of each round was put in a 1v1 to win a signed drumstick. The team + brothers played on your team, and the second round they switched sides, so u will play on the same team with all three brothers at one point.

THE ORDER:
1. Dodgeball
2. M&G
3. Masterclass Group Photos
4. Masterclass
